user_prompt_template:
As of {as_of}, is there a credible, recently-disclosed Schedule 13D activist filing on {company} (an investor crossing the 5% ownership threshold with stated intent to engage management or push for strategic change)? Score 4 (recent credible 13D with a clear stated activist agenda), 2 (rumored/unconfirmed activist interest), or 0 (no known activist involvement) — based on what was publicly known as of {as_of} only.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

As of {as_of}, is there a recent cluster of open-market insider buying at {company} (multiple executives/directors buying with their own money, not routine option-exercise-and-hold or 10b5-1 scheduled sales)? Score 3 (a real recent cluster buy), 1 (isolated/unclear single insider purchase), or 0 (no known insider buying, or only routine/scheduled activity) — based on what was publicly known as of {as_of} only.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

As of {as_of}, has {company} recently received a meaningful positive analyst rating upgrade or price-target raise (a real sentiment shift, not routine coverage-initiation noise)? Score 3 (a clear recent upgrade/target raise from a credible desk), 1 (mixed/unclear analyst sentiment), or 0 (no positive analyst action, or recent downgrades) — based on what was publicly known as of {as_of} only.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

As of {as_of}, did {company} raise its forward guidance at its most recent earnings report (a genuine signal of management confidence, distinct from merely beating a prior estimate — see d24_epsbeat for that separate criterion)? Score 3 (clear guidance raise), 1 (maintained/unclear guidance), or 0 (guidance cut or withdrawn) — based on what was publicly known as of {as_of} only.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

As of {as_of}, has {company} recently received (or does it have a near-term pending) a material regulatory approval, patent grant, or similar binary regulatory catalyst (FDA approval, patent issuance, licensing approval) relevant to its business? Score 4 (recent approval already secured), 2 (credible near-term pending decision, genuinely binary/uncertain), or 0 (no relevant regulatory catalyst) — based on what was publicly known as of {as_of} only.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

As of {as_of}, is there a credible M&A rumor, announced strategic-alternatives review, or acquisition approach involving {company} (credible = reported by mainstream financial press with named sources or company confirmation, not anonymous social-media speculation)? Score 4 (company has confirmed a process or a deal is announced), 2 (credible press-reported rumor, unconfirmed by the company), or 0 (no known M&A activity) — based on what was publicly known as of {as_of} only.

